        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued October 18 at 12:46PM CDT by NWS Tulsa OK</headline>
        <description>At 1246 PM CDT, Doppler radar indicated a strong thunderstorm near
Quapaw, moving northeast at 40 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down small tree limbs and blow
around unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation
is possible.

Locations in or near the path include...
Picher...                         Cardin...
Peoria...                         Commerce...
Narcissa...                       Ottawa...
Quapaw...                         Miami...
Treece...                         Welch...
Baxter Springs...

This includes Interstate 44 between mile markers 300 and 324.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

A Severe Thunderstorm Watch remains in effect until 600 PM CDT for
northeastern Oklahoma.</instruction>
